'''
1. Using Secrets (Recommended for Passwords)
You can define secrets via the Kestra UI or as environment variables. 
Via UI: Go to Namespaces -> Select your namespace -> Secrets tab -> Add a new secret (e.g., DB_PASSWORD).
Via Environment Variables: Define variables in your .env or Docker configuration with the SECRET_ prefix and base64-encoded values.
Example: SECRET_POSTGRES_PASSWORD=YWRtaW4= (which is "admin"). 
Updating your Flow:
Reference the secret using the {{ secret('KEY') }} function.
'''


SECRET_POSTGRES_PASSWORD=base64_encoded_postgres_password

DB_USER=username
DB_PASSWORD=password
DB_NAME=database_name

PGADMIN_USER=username
PGADMIN_PASSWORD=password

# Kestra API (used by CI/CD pipeline)
KESTRA_URL=http://localhost:8089
KESTRA_USER=admin@kestra.io
KESTRA_PASSWORD=Admin1234!

# Streamlit dashboard (uses DB_USER/DB_PASSWORD/DB_NAME above — no extra config needed)
